---
pagination:
  data: products
  size: 1
  alias: product
  resolve: values
permalink: "/products/{{ product.slug }}/"
layout: layouts/base.njk
eleventyComputed:
  title: "{{ product.name }}"
  description: "What {{ product.name }} contains now. Every fact is shown with its source, confidence and evidence level; anything not yet verified is withheld rather than asserted."
---
{% from "components/macros.njk" import sourcedValue, sourceNote, caveatBox, factCell %}

{#
  One server-rendered page per product. The src/_data/products/* cascade is an
  OBJECT keyed by filename, so the front-matter pagination uses resolve: values:
  default pagination over an object iterates its KEYS (strings), which would break
  every template (03a-RESEARCH.md Pattern 1 / Pitfall 2). Hyphenated keys
  (products.spike-01) are also invalid Nunjucks dot access; paginating over values
  sidesteps that. A1 is smoke-verified by asserting the product NAME (not a
  filename) renders on a built page.
#}

<h1>{{ product.name }}</h1>

<p class="lede">The current declared record for {{ product.name }}. Each value is shown through the trust component: a fact appears only once it has met the verification standard its claim type demands, and is otherwise marked "not yet verified; withheld".</p>

{#
  Sections follow the LOCKED D-05 order: Ingredients, Nutrition, Allergens,
  Manufacturer, Sources, Recipe history. This plan (03a-03) authors Ingredients,
  Manufacturer, Sources and Recipe history. Plan 04 inserts the Nutrition and
  Allergens h2 sections between Ingredients and Manufacturer, in that order; the
  placeholder comment below marks where they slot in so the outline stays gap-free.
#}

<section id="ingredients" aria-labelledby="ingredients-heading">
  <h2 id="ingredients-heading">Ingredients</h2>
  <p>The current declared ingredients list. This is the sourced recipe of record; it is not broken out into individual ingredient entries here.</p>
  {%- if product.ingredientsText %}
  {{ sourcedValue(product.ingredientsText, sources.sources, "Declared ingredients", "", "product") }}
  {%- else %}
  <p class="example">No declared ingredients list has been sourced for this product yet.</p>
  {%- endif %}
</section>

{#
  Nutrition (PROD-01, D-06 / F4). A real accessible <table> of the nine fixed
  back-of-pack figures in schema order, distinguishing THREE conditions the
  reader must never see conflated:
    - key NOT in nutrition  -> "Not recorded" (a figure the archive never held)
    - key present, withheld  -> "Not yet verified" (held, but not through the gate)
    - key present, published  -> the value, via factCell.
  The absent/present distinction uses an "if key in nutrition" membership test
  (metadata, NEVER .value); the value/status cell renders only
  through factCell (the R-31 boundary, inside macros.njk), so no raw fact value
  can reach a reader. Each recorded figure carries a full provenance block below
  the table at id="nutrition-{key}" with tabindex="-1", so a "see source" status
  link moves keyboard/screen-reader focus there (G2, WCAG 2.4.3). The table has
  three short columns and wraps by default (no white-space:nowrap, short status
  text), so it reflows with no horizontal scroll at 320px / 400% zoom (G1).
#}
{%- set nutrition = product.nutrition or {} %}
{%- set nutritionRows = [
  { key: "energyKj", label: "Energy (kJ)", unit: "kJ" },
  { key: "energyKcal", label: "Energy (kcal)", unit: "kcal" },
  { key: "fat", label: "Fat", unit: "g" },
  { key: "saturates", label: "Saturates", unit: "g" },
  { key: "carbohydrate", label: "Carbohydrate", unit: "g" },
  { key: "sugars", label: "Sugars", unit: "g" },
  { key: "fibre", label: "Fibre", unit: "g" },
  { key: "protein", label: "Protein", unit: "g" },
  { key: "salt", label: "Salt", unit: "g" }
] %}
<section id="nutrition" aria-labelledby="nutrition-heading">
  <h2 id="nutrition-heading">Nutrition</h2>
  <p>The back-of-pack nutrition declaration per 100g. Each recorded figure is shown through the trust component. A figure marked "Not recorded" is one we have never sourced; it is not the same as a figure we hold but have not yet verified.</p>
  <table class="nutrition-table">
    <caption>Nutrition per 100g</caption>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th scope="col">Nutrient</th>
        <th scope="col">Per 100g</th>
        <th scope="col">Status</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {%- for row in nutritionRows %}
      <tr>
        <th scope="row">{{ row.label }}</th>
        {%- if row.key in nutrition %}
        {%- set nd = nutrition[row.key] | factState(sources.sources, "product") %}
        <td>{{ factCell(nutrition[row.key], sources.sources, row.unit, "product") }}</td>
        <td>
          {%- if nd.publishable %}<a href="#nutrition-{{ row.key }}">see source</a>
          {%- elif nd.contested %}<a href="#nutrition-{{ row.key }}">sources disagree</a>
          {%- else %}<a href="#nutrition-{{ row.key }}">sources being checked</a>{% endif %}
        </td>
        {%- else %}
        <td class="nutrition-table__absent">Not recorded</td>
        <td class="nutrition-table__absent">-</td>
        {%- endif %}
      </tr>
      {%- endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {%- if nutrition | length %}
  <h3 id="nutrition-sources-heading">Nutrition sources</h3>
  <p>The source and date for each recorded figure above.</p>
  {%- for row in nutritionRows %}
  {%- if row.key in nutrition %}
  <div id="nutrition-{{ row.key }}" tabindex="-1" class="nutrition-source">
    {{ sourcedValue(nutrition[row.key], sources.sources, row.label, row.unit, "product") }}
  </div>
  {%- endif %}
  {%- endfor %}
  {%- endif %}
</section>

{#
  Allergens (PROD-09, D-12, highest-stakes). The section fails SAFE toward
  warning, never toward reassurance. Each row branches on presence AND the
  DERIVED provenance state (factState), NEVER on provenance.value: the fail-safe
  wording is chosen by the pure, unit-tested allergenLine helper so "a withheld
  absent claim never reads as safe" is a build-time invariant, not a hand-checked
  template branch. The human-readable allergen name is interpolated from
  allergens.json into the helper's {allergen} placeholder. All row text is
  #0b0c0c black; the #d4351c red is a bar/border SECOND cue only (it fails 4.5:1
  as text on the panel), applied to every row EXCEPT a published "absent" one
  (uncertainty about absence is treated as risk). The standing allergen-safety
  caveat sits at the top of the section on any page showing allergens. F5 (LOCK
  option a): an allergen with no record is simply not listed, covered by the
  standing caveat; a missing allergen must never read as absent.
#}
<section id="allergens" aria-labelledby="allergens-heading">
  <h2 id="allergens-heading">Allergens</h2>
  {%- if product.allergens and product.allergens.length %}
  {{ caveatBox("Allergen information can change. Always check the current product packaging. Do not rely on this archive for allergy safety.", "Allergen safety") }}
  <dl class="allergen-list">
    {%- for item in product.allergens %}
    {%- set ap = item.provenance | factState(sources.sources, "product") %}
    {%- set aName = (allergens.allergens | findBy("id", item.allergen)).name or item.allergen %}
    {%- set warning = not (item.presence == "absent" and ap.publishable) %}
    <div class="allergen-list__item{% if warning %} allergen-list__item--warning{% endif %}">
      <dt class="allergen-list__name">{{ aName }}</dt>
      <dd>
        <p>{{ item.presence | allergenLine(ap.publishable) | replace("{allergen}", aName) }}</p>
        {%- if ap.publishable %}
        {{ sourcedValue(item.provenance, sources.sources, "Source and date", "", "product") }}
        {%- endif %}
      </dd>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </dl>
  {%- else %}
  <p class="example">No allergen information has been sourced for this product yet. Always check the current product packaging.</p>
  {%- endif %}
</section>

<section id="manufacturer" aria-labelledby="manufacturer-heading">
  <h2 id="manufacturer-heading">Manufacturer</h2>
  {%- if product.manufacturer %}
  {{ sourcedValue(product.manufacturer, sources.sources, "Made by", "", "product") }}
  {%- else %}
  <p class="example">No manufacturer has been sourced for this product yet.</p>
  {%- endif %}
</section>

{#
  Sources roll-up (PROD-04, D-07): the page-level list of the distinct source
  records cited by this page's facts. The per-fact "Source and date" disclosure
  still lives on each fact above; this is the consolidated view. The ids are
  collected and de-duplicated (first-seen order) by the pure citedSourceIds filter
  over ALL fact-bearing fields (manufacturer, ingredientsText, nutrition figures,
  allergen provenance) - the collection lives in lib/ because Nunjucks {% set %}
  inside a for loop does not persist across iterations, so it cannot be done
  correctly in-template. Source names and urls are ingested and external, so they
  are never piped through | safe; external links carry rel="noopener" (threat
  T-03a-03-02).
#}
{%- set citedIds = product | citedSourceIds %}
<section id="sources" aria-labelledby="sources-heading">
  <h2 id="sources-heading">Sources</h2>
  {%- if citedIds.length %}
  <p>The sources cited by the facts on this page. Each fact above also shows its own source and date behind its "Source and date" disclosure.</p>
  <ul class="source-roll">
    {%- for id in citedIds %}
    {%- set s = sources.sources | findBy("id", id) %}
    <li>
      {%- if s %}
      {% if s.url %}<a href="{{ s.url }}" rel="noopener">{{ s.name }}</a>{% else %}{{ s.name }}{% endif %}{% if s.jurisdiction %} ({{ s.jurisdiction }}){% endif %}.
      {%- else %}
      Unresolved source reference: {{ id }}.
      {%- endif %}
    </li>
    {%- endfor %}
  </ul>
  {%- else %}
  <p class="example">No sources have been cited on this page yet.</p>
  {%- endif %}
</section>

{#
  Recipe history (PROD-02/03, SC3). Events are joined by the timelineByProduct
  reverse index (global from 03a-01). Each event's documentedChange and
  statedReason are sourced facts, rendered through the trust component with
  entityType "timeline" (historical facts, never stale). labelledInference is NOT
  a fact (it has no sources or claimType) and is rendered as a labelled
  illustration paragraph ONLY, never through the trust component (threat
  T-03a-03-03). Where a product has no sourced change events, the honest empty
  state renders (SC3, "absent, not a broken stub"), never a withheld or error
  card. The conditional "full timeline" link renders only where a Phase 8 timeline
  page exists (none do yet, so it is omitted).
#}
<section id="recipe-history" aria-labelledby="recipe-history-heading">
  <h2 id="recipe-history-heading">Recipe history</h2>
  {%- set events = timelineByProduct[product.id] %}
  {%- if events and events.length %}
  <p>Sourced, dated changes to this product's formulation. Each change shows its source, date and confidence; a value that its sources genuinely disagree on is shown as contested, with both positions.</p>
  {%- for e in events %}
  <article class="change-event">
    <h3>
      {%- if e.date.from or e.date.to %}
      Changed {{ e.date.from }} to {{ e.date.to }}{% if e.date.basis %} ({{ e.date.basis }}){% endif %}
      {%- else %}
      Changed {{ e.date | readableDate }}
      {%- endif %}
    </h3>
    {%- for c in e.changes %}
    {%- if c.documentedChange %}{{ sourcedValue(c.documentedChange, sources.sources, "Documented change", "", "timeline") }}{% endif %}
    {%- if c.statedReason %}{{ sourcedValue(c.statedReason, sources.sources, "Stated reason", "", "timeline") }}{% endif %}
    {%- if c.labelledInference %}
    <p class="example"><strong>Labelled inference:</strong> {{ c.labelledInference.text }}</p>
    {%- endif %}
    {%- endfor %}
  </article>
  {%- endfor %}
  {%- else %}
  <div class="example">
    <h3>No recipe changes recorded yet</h3>
    <p>We have not yet sourced and verified any formulation changes for this product. When we do, they will appear here, each with its source and date.</p>
  </div>
  {%- endif %}
</section>
